===Etymology===
From a {{etyl|cmn|en}} term which means "mountains' west", referring to the province's location west of the Taihang Mountains.

===Pronunciation===
* {{IPA|/ˈʃɑnˈʃi/|lang=en}}

===Alternative forms===
* Chinese: [[山西]]
* Pinyin: Shānxī
* Wade-Giles: Shan-hsi
* Its one-character abbreviation is Jin ([[晋]] [[pinyin]] jìn), after the state of Jin that existed here during the Spring and Autumn Period.
* Chinese Postal Map Romanization: Shansi.

===Proper noun===
{{en-proper noun}}

# A [[province]] in the northern part of the [[People's Republic of China]].

